    g?
        Because kidney disease is more common in people of those ethnic origins, so there is a higher demand of kidneys than for people of white ethnic origin; but, there are not many donors from those communities, so there is a lower supply, so kidney donors are particularly required. Also, it is not likely, due to differences in genetic makeup, that people of these ethnic origins would be able to receive kidneys from people of white origin.
