            Because there may be other limiting factors e.g. temperature once the crop has absorbed all required minerals
        ii? [definition of eutrophication, general]
            Applying more water than needed may lead to flooding or the soil becoming loose or saturated, potentially killing any insects or animal which burrow in the soil.

            Applying too much nitrogen fertilizer may lead to eutrophication. Combined with the excess water, which will carry the nitrogen fertilizer to nearby water bodies such as rivers, this may lead to excess growth of e.g. algae which will consume much of the oxygen in the water, starving other aquatic life. This may harm the food-chain as this may mean that some fishes' population will decrease..
        
    b.
        Carbon monoxide binds irreversibly to haemoglobin in red blood cells, and prevents oxygen from binding to said haemoglobin. Too much exposure can lead to not enough oxygen being supplied to body cells for respiration and eventual suffocation.
